text: Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?" You look down and see a bee in a suit. "Do you talk? Did you just talk to me?" I asked. "Yes, Your Majesty. I come from that hive over there in a tree and we bees think you should be our queen" "I'm not a bee, I'm a human. And I'm allergic to bees!" "Yes, we know, but we think you're perfect for the job." said the little bee." "Well I do like your little suit. Maybe I will consider. What do I have to do to be your queen?", I asked. "You just have to do one thing. You have to make a wish and we will grant it." I thought that sure sounded easy. But I didn't know what wish to make. After a few minutes I finally decided. "I wish I could fly like a bee." I said. "Your wish is granted." said the little bee. And I grew wings and became like a bee. I was able to fly around and it was fantastic! "So what do you think?" asked the Bee. Do you like being the queen bee?" "Yes, I love it!" I said. but then I started shrinking. "What is happening?" I asked. And before I knew it, I was the same size as the little bee. I had become an actual bee. "Wait this isn't what I signed up for!" I exclaimed. "You said you wanted to fly like a bee." "I know but I didn't want to be a bee!" Little did I know that by making that wish I had resigned myself to a life of being the queen bee. I was stuck as a bee for the rest of my life. But I made the best of it and I was a really good queen bee.
